<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idcaa1cf13-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70" identifier="/us/usc/t49/s5306"><num value="5306">§ 5306.</num><heading> Private enterprise participation in metropolitan planning and transportation improvement programs and relationship to other limitations</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idcaa1cf14-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70" identifier="/us/usc/t49/s5306/a"><num value="a">(a)</num><heading> <inline class="small-caps">Private Enterprise Participation</inline>.—</heading><content>A plan or program required by section 5303, 5304, or 5305 of this title shall encourage to the maximum extent feasible, as determined by local policies, criteria, and decisionmaking, the participation of private enterprise. If equipment or a facility already being used in an urban area is to be acquired under this chapter, the program shall provide that it be improved so that it will better serve the transportation needs of the area.</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idcaa1cf15-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70" identifier="/us/usc/t49/s5306/b"><num value="b">(b)</num><heading> <inline class="small-caps">Relationship to Other Limitations</inline>.—</heading><chapeau>Sections 5303–5305 of this title do not authorize—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idcaa1cf16-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70" identifier="/us/usc/t49/s5306/b/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> a metropolitan planning organization to impose a legal requirement on a transportation facility, provider, or project not eligible under this chapter or title 23; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idcaa1cf17-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70" identifier="/us/usc/t49/s5306/b/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> intervention in the management of a transportation authority.</content>
</paragraph>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idcaa1cf18-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70">(<ref href="/us/pl/103/272/s1/d">Pub. L. 103–272, § 1(d)</ref>, <date date="1994-07-05">July 5, 1994</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/108/795">108 Stat. 795</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/109/59/tIII/s3008">Pub. L. 109–59, title III, § 3008</ref>, <date date="2005-08-10">Aug. 10, 2005</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/119/1568">119 Stat. 1568</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
